SafetyBar.MotionGroup.Physical.Explanati: {{motionGroupId}} is a physical robot controller. Safety precautions are active for the movement of this robot.
SafetyBar.MotionGroup.Virtual.Explanatio: <1>{{motionGroupId}}</1> is a virtual robot controller with no physical counterpart. It can be freely manipulated without safety precautions.
SafetyBar.OperationMode.Auto.Explanation: Automatic operation mode active. Automated movement without manual confirmation enabled.
SafetyBar.OperationMode.Error.Explanatio: Failed to get operation mode. Use the original control panel to resolve the error.
SafetyBar.OperationMode.Manual.Explanati: The robot controller is in manual operation mode. On a physical robot, this generally indicates that an enabling switch must be held for the robot to move successfully.
The robot controller has entered an unexpected safety state.
SafetyBar.SafetyState.ManualActionRequir: The robot controller has entered a safety state requiring manual action to resolve.
SafetyBar.SafetyState.Normal.Explanation: The robot controller is in a safe state. Robot movement is enabled.
SafetyBar.SafetyState.Stop.Explanation.l: The robot controller has entered a stop state. Movement is no longer possible until the stop state is resolved.
SafetyBar.StopState.Estop.Explanation.lb: An emergency stop of the robot controller has been triggered. Movement of the robot is no longer possible until the estop is released.
